Remove repo-root package.json so Vercel uses the right one

The Vercel build kept failing with `vite: command not found` because
its install step printed `added 1 package in 1s` -- it was installing
the *repo-root* package.json (one dependency: @stripe/stripe-js)
instead of `client-frontend/package.json` (which actually has Vite
and friends in its devDependencies).

Even with a Root Directory of `client-frontend` set in the Vercel UI,
the presence of a top-level package.json was enough to confuse the
modern `vercel build` flow into installing from the wrong place.

The root package.json was just a convenience wrapper exposing
`npm run start:admin` / `start:client` / `install:*` aliases. Local
development now goes through Docker Compose (`docker compose up`) or
through `cd client-frontend && npm start`, so the wrapper is no longer
needed.

The single dependency it declared (@stripe/stripe-js) is already a
real dependency of client-frontend, so nothing is lost.
